                    'rmin', 'tmmn', 'tmmx', 'vpd', 'vs', 
                    'Snow Water Equivalent (in) Start of Day Values',
                    'slope', 'curvature', 'aspect', 'eastness',
                    'northness']
chunk_size = 1000000

# Create an empty DataFrame to store the result
result_df = pd.DataFrame()

# Get the total number of chunks for tqdm progress bar
total_chunks = sum(1 for _ in pd.read_csv(input_csv, usecols=selected_columns, chunksize=chunk_size))

# Read the CSV file in chunks and extract the selected columns
for chunk in tqdm(pd.read_csv(input_csv, usecols=selected_columns, chunksize=chunk_size), total=total_chunks, desc='Processing'):
    result_df = pd.concat([result_df, chunk], ignore_index=True)

# Replace 'output.csv' with the desired output file name

result_df.rename(columns={"Snow Water Equivalent (in) Start of Day Values": "swe_value"}, inplace=True)

# Write the selected columns to a new CSV file
result_df.to_csv(output_csv, index=False)
